<p>A tanker truck carrying gasoline exploded on Tuesday in the Bida area of Niger State in north‑central Nigeria, leaving reports of dozens killed and many more injured; outlets cite between 31 and at least 38 fatalities so far [thehindu.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][japantoday.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][apnews.com#1]. Authorities and news agencies say the blast produced mass casualties and significant burn injuries, and local emergency services responded to the scene [apnews.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Officials’ casualty figures vary across reports as investigators and first responders continued work at the site [aljazeera.com#1][apnews.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/e90IKVlsdXeuhhtibiPqN-DbK4uHm9PXJ7bGEwNk-uNG_LWZlCv1syBhDhZGvnZa2ePc2lhu1zD3MWz28rEaaXSCD2tblomZFVFXNLXbNlVmWZF_Uz591URprslQrllLfI_epmI61qglstA' alt='Fuel truck explodes in Nigeria and kills at least 31 people, police say' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Immediate cause: Witnesses and reporters said people rushed to collect fuel from an overturned tanker and the vapour or leaked gasoline ignited, causing the blast that engulfed those nearby [bbc.com#1].</li><li>Varying tolls: Different agencies quoted different death counts — police wires reported at least 31, the federal road safety agency cited 35, and one wire service put the toll at least 38 — reflecting rapidly changing figures at the scene [thehindu.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][apnews.com#1].</li><li>Injuries and damage: Reports say dozens were wounded, many with burns requiring emergency treatment, and survivors were taken to nearby hospitals for care [apnews.com#1][bbc.com#1].</li><li>Recurring risk: News outlets note that transporting petroleum by road is common in Nigeria, and deadly incidents involving fuel spills or explosions have repeatedly occurred in similar circumstances [aljazeera.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Nigeria police: Police reports say a tanker laden with gasoline exploded in a north‑central area, initially putting the death toll at 31. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/nigeria-gas-tank-explosion-many-killed-october-21-2025/article70187847.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Federal Road Safety Agency: The agency provided a toll of 35 dead in its statement as first responders continued recovery operations. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/nigerian-fuel-tanker-explosion-kills-35-road-safety-agency-says'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Local witnesses: Residents described people crowding to collect spilled fuel from the overturned tanker moments before the explosion engulfed them. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c93dnd49l0jo'>BBC</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/nigerian-fuel-tanker-explosion-kills-35-road-safety-agency-says'>Nigerian fuel tanker explosion kills 35, road safety agency says</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/nigeria-gas-tank-explosion-many-killed-october-21-2025/article70187847.ece'>Truck laden with gasoline explodes in Nigeria and kills at least 31 people, police say</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/truck-laden-with-gasoline-explodes-in-nigeria-and-kills-at-least-31-people-police-say'>Truck laden with gasoline explodes in Nigeria, killing at least 31 people</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/fuel-truck-explodes-nigeria-kills-31-people-police-126735134'>Fuel truck explodes in Nigeria and kills at least 31 people, police say</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c93dnd49l0jo'>Dozens killed in Nigeria fuel tanker explosion</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://apnews.com/article/nigeria-truck-explodes-gasoline-residents-killed-923f073a0cf0436e4ff73bfb15d6081f'>At least 38 people are killed and dozens of others are injured when a tanker truck transporting gasoline crashes and explodes in Bida, Nigeria